<TITLE> Illegal foreign SIMs recovered from trade fair </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 5 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh Telecommunication Regulatory Commission has recovered unapproved SIM cards from the Dhaka International Trade Fair. BTRC and RAB officials discovered the SIM cards belonging to foreign company World SIM after searching the stall of Awal Call Centre, said a BTRC press release. People working at the call centre were caught in the act of selling the SIM cards, said BTRC. "Steps are being taken to halt irregularities in the telecom sector and BTRC will not hesitate to take punitive measures against any activity that is in contravention to the Bangladesh telecommunication act," BTRC chairman Monjurul Alam told bdnews24.com, "I hope that law breakers will start respecting the law regarding illegal VOIP and other issues on their own will," said the retired major general. The BTRC statement said the SIM cards of a foreign organisation were being sold without BTRC permission and with the aim of deceiving subscribers. A case has been lodged with Adabar police. bdnews
